defaultAppendix - Photographic Evidence of destruction of Long Causeway in Recent Yearsdefault1.defaultIn the 4 photos below, the arrow points at the same rock each time.  The destruction of the track by motorised vehicles was already well underway by 2004, but the photos below evidence how severely this process has continued in the past 9 years.  It can be seen how the surface is being worn away and rocks that should form the foundation of the track are being exposed. Also, a drainage pipe has been exposed, risking inevitable damage and a consequent increase in water erosion.  Also, much of the sand and pebbles that made the track smoother in 2004 have now become rubble, making the track far harder to walk - and impossible for horses:
